{#
 How to use this component:
 
 1) Variables building an unordered list:
 - extraClasses: (string) Optional set of classes to add to the list.
  If nothing is supplied, `ecl-list` class comes by default.
 - list: (iterable) A list of items.
  List items have the following structure:
  {
    modifier: (string) Obligatory modifier.
    value: (string) Obligatory value for the list item.
  }

  2) Variables building a single link:
  - link: (structure) Obligatory data for the link itself.
  {
    target: (string) Obligatory link target.
    modifier: (string) Obligatory modifier.
    extraClasses: (string) Optional classes on top of defaults.
    title: (string) Obligatory link title.
  }

  3) Variables building a span - this is a default output if the preceding fail.
  - modifier: (string) Obligatory modifier.
  - text: (text) The textual value.
#}

{# If there is a list, make a list #}
{% if list is defined and list is iterable %}
<ul class="{{ listExtraClasses ?: 'ecl-list' }}">
  {% for listItem in list %}
  <li class="ecl-icon-social {{ listItem.modifier }}">{{ listItem.value }}</li>
  {% endfor %}
</ul>
{# If there is a link, it's a link #}
{% elseif link is defined %}
<a
  href="{{ link.target }}"
  class="ecl-link ecl-icon-social {{ modifier }} {{ link.extraClasses }}"
  >{{ link.title }}</a>
{% else %}
{# Provide a span as a fallback #}
<span class='ecl-icon-social {{ modifier }}'>{{ text }}</span>
{% endif %}
